Getting time for particular timezone.

To get both current date and time datetime.now() function of datetime module is used.

importing datetime module for now().
import datetime  

Timezone are defined in pytz library.
import  pytz 

To get the date time for a particular timezone now()function takes timezone as input to give timezone oriented output time.
current_time=datetime.datetime.now(pytz.timezone('asia/kolkata'))

Dispaly the data
print("current time:",current_time)
